# Vite / React / Ant Design best practices

## React Router

- Keep route components in `src/pages/`.
- Prefer route-level code splitting (`React.lazy`) when pages grow.
- Keep navigation state in the URL where it improves shareability (query params, path params).

## Ant Design

- Prefer consistent design via `ConfigProvider` theme tokens (see `src/app/theme.ts`) over one-off styling.
- Prefer AntD layout primitives (`Row`, `Col`, `Space`, `Typography`, `Layout`) for alignment/spacing consistency.

## Performance + DX

- Avoid creating new arrays/objects in JSX props when it causes rerenders; move stable values to `consts.ts` or `useMemo` where needed.
- Prefer named handlers (`const onClick = () => {}`) only when reused; inline lambdas are ok unless they cause measurable perf issues.
- Keep CSS scoped (prefer CSS Modules) to avoid global leakage as the app grows.

